All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable
public class ServiceCapabilities
extends Capabilities

This class defines capabilities for Services. The simplest way to access a capability is to use one of the predefined capability indexes provided in this class, for example, to find out if a service has attribute querying, and if enabled, you could use code such as the following


       ServerProxy server;
       ServerCapabilities capabilities = server.getCapabilities();
       Capability capability = capabilities.getCapability(ServerCapabilities.ATTRIBUTE_QUERY);
       if (capability.isAvailable() && capability.isEnabled()) {
           ....
       }
